Citizen journalism, where individuals without formal journalistic training report news and share information, has both advantages and disadvantages.

**Advantages:**

- **Diverse Perspectives:** Citizen journalists often highlight stories and viewpoints overlooked by traditional media, enriching public discourse. ([educationalwave.com](https://www.educationalwave.com/pros-and-cons-of-citizen-journalism/?utm_source=openai))

- **Immediate Reporting:** With widespread access to smartphones and social media, citizen journalists can provide real-time updates on unfolding events, offering timely information. ([educationalwave.com](https://www.educationalwave.com/pros-and-cons-of-citizen-journalism/?utm_source=openai))

- **Community Engagement:** By involving ordinary individuals in news reporting, citizen journalism fosters greater community involvement and transparency. ([educationalwave.com](https://www.educationalwave.com/pros-and-cons-of-citizen-journalism/?utm_source=openai))

**Disadvantages:**

- **Accuracy and Credibility Issues:** Lacking formal training, citizen journalists may inadvertently spread unverified or biased information, leading to misinformation. ([educationalwave.com](https://www.educationalwave.com/pros-and-cons-of-citizen-journalism/?utm_source=openai))

- **Ethical Concerns:** Without adherence to established journalistic ethics, citizen journalists might unintentionally invade privacy or sensationalize events, potentially causing harm. ([researchcage.com](https://researchcage.com/2023/05/04/the-disadvantage-of-citizen-journalism/?utm_source=openai))

- **Legal and Safety Risks:** Unaware of legal protocols or safety measures, citizen journalists may face legal challenges or personal danger, especially when reporting on sensitive issues. ([medium.com](https://medium.com/%40alligeewriting/the-challenges-and-impact-of-citizen-journalism-training-risks-and-responsibilities-a56bc019325d?utm_source=openai))

In summary, while citizen journalism democratizes information dissemination and brings attention to underreported stories, it also presents challenges related to accuracy, ethics, and safety. Balancing these factors is crucial for its effective contribution to the media landscape. 

